{
  "texts": [
    "The convolutional layers are distributed: 2 of 32, 2 of 64, 3 of 128, 3 of 256, and finally, 9 of 512 divided into blocks of 3SELU(x) = x if x > 0 α • (exp(x) -1) if x ≤ 0 Fig.",
    "Data balanced Synthetic minority over-sampling technique (SMOTE)We have a very unbalanced data set in the binary classification, so data balancing is performed with SMOTE.",
    "This works in such a way that synthesized data can be generated using similar neighboring samples and linear combinations between them; this helps to increase the data of the minority class, allowing the model to learn the patterns of the unbalanced course better [28].",
    "Adaptive synthetic sampling (ADASYN)It is used to create synthesized data from the minority class to balance the data.",
    "It focuses on generating synthesized data in feature regions where the minority class examples are few, helping the model better capture the class data with fewer data, and avoiding overgeneralization of the model [29]."
  ]
}